<item>
            <title>[SPR-6475] Combining ControllerClassNameHandlerMapping and @RequestMapping with relative value on Controller method  doesn&apos;t work anymore</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6475</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The controller beans xml file contains:&lt;br/&gt;
---------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;context:component-scan base-package=&quot;org.example.web&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;bean class=&quot;org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.support.ControllerClassNameHandlerMapping&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Controller class:&lt;br/&gt;
---------------------&lt;br/&gt;
package org.example.web;&lt;br/&gt;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;&lt;br/&gt;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Controller&lt;br/&gt;
public class ArticlesController {&lt;br/&gt;
  @RequestMapping(&quot;all&quot;) // all == a relative URL&lt;br/&gt;
  public String findAll() &lt;/p&gt;
{	
    return &quot;/WEB-INF/JSP/allArticles.jsp&quot;;
  }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spring 2.5&lt;br/&gt;
----------&lt;br/&gt;
A GET request with the URL /articles/all was processed by the function findAll&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spring 3.0 RC2&lt;br/&gt;
--------------&lt;br/&gt;
A GET request with the URL /articles/all produces HTTP 404 error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
